author: Missy Wilkinson, Amy Rose Spiegel, Casey Johnston
title: New Orleans ER Workers Say Hospitals Are Verging on 'Systemic Collapse'
description: In Louisiana, COVID-19 is spreading faster than it has anywhere else in the world. The state is home to some of the nation's sickest and poorest people, and health care professionals fear the virus will overwhelm emergency resources in as soon as a week.
content: On Sunday, March 15, many New Orleanians were throwing crawfish boils, catering to Bourbon Streets tourists, and grumbling over the cancellation of the St. Patricks Day parade. At the time, Louisiana had 91 confirmed cases of coronavirus. A week later, Louisi… [+6686 chars]
